# LiVEiT® Minimum Size

The LiVEiT® logo must always remain clear, legible and recognisable regardless of where it is displayed.

Using the logo below an appropriate size can reduce readability and weaken brand recognition.

This document defines the minimum sizing guidance for the official LiVEiT® logo family.

---

# Purpose

Minimum sizing ensures that the logo remains:

* Readable
* Recognisable
* Professional
* Consistent
* Accessible

The logo should never be reduced to a size where important details become difficult to distinguish.

---

# Digital Applications

For websites, applications and digital interfaces, the logo should always be displayed at a size that preserves clarity.

General recommendations:

| Logo Type        | Minimum Width |
| ---------------- | ------------- |
| Primary Wordmark | 120 px        |
| Horizontal Logo  | 140 px        |
| Icon Only        | 24 px         |

These values provide a practical baseline and may be increased where space permits.

---

# Print Applications

For printed materials, the logo should never be reproduced below a size where it becomes difficult to read.

General guidance:

| Logo Type        | Minimum Width |
| ---------------- | ------------- |
| Primary Wordmark | 30 mm         |
| Horizontal Logo  | 35 mm         |
| Icon Only        | 8 mm          |

High-quality vector artwork should always be used for print production.

---

# Small Interfaces

In applications where space is limited, such as:

* Mobile navigation
* Toolbars
* Browser interfaces
* Application launchers

the approved icon only version may be used instead of the full wordmark.

The icon should never be substituted with an unofficial graphic.

---

# Responsive Design

Responsive layouts should preserve logo clarity across all screen sizes.

If available space becomes restricted:

* Reduce the logo proportionally.
* Maintain the required clear space.
* Use an approved alternative logo where appropriate.
* Never compress or distort the artwork.

---

# High Resolution Displays

Modern displays provide increased pixel density.

Even on high-resolution screens, the logo should not be displayed below the recommended minimum sizes.

Scaling should always preserve sharp rendering.

---

# Large Format Applications

For banners, presentations and large displays:

* Use official vector artwork.
* Scale proportionally.
* Preserve clear space.
* Maintain colour accuracy.

There is no maximum logo size provided that the artwork remains proportionally scaled.

---

# Incorrect Usage

Do not:

* Reduce the logo until text becomes unreadable.
* Compress the logo to fit a space.
* Stretch the artwork.
* Crop the logo.
* Substitute unofficial versions.
* Use low-resolution raster images where vector artwork is available.

These practices reduce the quality and consistency of the LiVEiT® visual identity.

---

# Best Practice

When selecting a logo size:

* Prioritise readability.
* Maintain proportional scaling.
* Preserve the required clear space.
* Choose the appropriate logo variation for the available space.
* Test visibility on the intended device or medium.

If there is any doubt, increase the size rather than reduce it.

A clearly visible logo strengthens recognition and maintains the professional appearance of the LiVEiT® Framework.
